-- Ford says to launch four new hybrids by 2012
-- 
-- Sun Jan 11, 2009 12:51pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/11/us-ford-hybrids-sb-idUSTRE50A23C20090111

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) said on Sunday it plans to introduce four new hybrids in North America by 2012. 

 Highlights: * CEO Mulally says 2009 promises to be challenging, restructuring on track * Product chief says will have a small electric car ready for launch in 2011 that would get 100 miles to a charge * Product chief says electric car sales to be focused on urban markets with initial sales of 5,000 to 10,000 units * Product chief says to develop new small electric car jointly with Magna International * Says will launch a plug-in hybrid by 2012 * Says will launch an electric commercial van in 2010